You have to use `@JsonManagedReference` and `@JsonBackReference` at the same time which I don&#39;t see in your source code. 

`@JsonManagedReference` - Using this , Jackson takes the forward part of the reference (e.g. your `Set&lt;Attendance&gt; attendance` in `Lesson` class), and converts it in a json-like storage format; this is the so-called marshalling process.


`@JsonBackReference` -  With this, Jackson looks for the back part of the reference (e.g. `Lesson lesson` in `Attendance` class) and leaves it as it is, not serializing it.

Try the below and it should work.

