Apply an exclusion from the test dependency (in example below - javafaker has been used to illustrate) that is trying to download the ```snakeyaml-2.0-android.jar``` artifact and request the one that exists:

```kotlin
dependencies {
    testImplementation(&quot;com.github.javafaker:javafaker:1.0.2&quot;) {
        exclude(group = &quot;org.yaml&quot;, module = &quot;snakeyaml&quot;)
    }
    testImplementation(&quot;org.yaml:snakeyaml:2.0&quot;)
}
```

Firstly open `build.gradle` file of java  project and then in the `dependencies` find where `snakeyaml`  is declared. 


After that you can exclude groups like this  :

    dependencies {
        // ... other dependencies
        compile(&#39;org.yaml:snakeyaml:2.0&#39;) {
            exclude group: &#39;org.yaml&#39;, module: &#39;snakeyaml-android&#39;
        }
        // ... other dependencies
